Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for Next.js App Router project

## Changes Made:

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package (v2.0.1)
- Updated package.json with the new dependency
- Updated package-lock.json with resolved dependencies

### 2. Analytics Integration
Modified: `src/app/layout.tsx`
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component to the root layout, placed right after the Toaster component within the body tag
- This follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router projects

## Implementation Details:

The implementation follows the latest official Vercel Web Analytics quickstart guide (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart):

1. Installed the @vercel/analytics package using npm (the project's package manager)
2. Added the Analytics component from '@vercel/analytics/next' to the root layout file
3. Placed the component within the body tag as recommended for Next.js App Router

## Verification:

- ✅ Build completed successfully (no errors)
- ✅ ESLint passes (only pre-existing font warning, unrelated to changes)
- ✅ TypeScript compilation successful
- ✅ All lock files updated appropriately

## Next Steps:

To enable analytics in production:
1. Navigate to the Analytics section in your Vercel project dashboard
2. Click the "Enable" button for Web Analytics
3. Deploy the application to Vercel
4. Verify setup by checking browser Network tab for requests from `/<unique-path>/view` when visiting pages

The Analytics component will automatically track page views and web vitals once deployed to Vercel.
